parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the brake lights do not function
smoke emerges from under the hood
the vehicle surges forward or backward
and the speed control indicator light on the dashboard is not functioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire sidewall separation can cause a loss of tire pressure, leading to a blowout, loss of control, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure Due to Manufacturing Defects
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure due to manufacturing defects can cause a loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
Inadequate tire replacement and reimbursement can lead to continued use of defective tires, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The dealer does not have replacement tires
the manufacturer refuses to reimburse for tire replacement
the consumer is forced to replace tires at their own expense.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, loss of vehicle functionality, and safety risks to occupants.
symptoms: Smoke or flames from under the hood
and warning lights on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning door locks and latches can cause safety risks, as occupants may become trapped in the vehicle.
Airbag system failures can cause safety risks, as the airbag system may not deploy properly in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag warning light flashing or staying on
and corrosion of the wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Various issues can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and safety risks to occupants.

The failure of the 5R55E transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents, especially when merging into traffic or driving uphill. This can result in a loss of control, increasing the risk of crashes and injuries.
symptoms: the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission makes a whining or knocking noise
the vehicle rolls backward on an incline
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
